modules.description: This module provides asynchronous operations for interacting with Slack's REST API, focusing on session management, channel and message manipulation, file handling, and OAuth integration. It works with structured types like `session`, `timestamp`, `message`, `user`, `channel`, and `attachment`, alongside error variants for handling Slack API failures. Typical use cases include building Slack bots that send/receive messages, manage channel memberships, upload files, authenticate via OAuth, and search or archive conversations.
